<A HREF='B20C003.htm'>Proverbs 3</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The            
Proverbs</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER>   
<TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter    
4</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>   
Hear, ye children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know              
understanding.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>
For I give you good doctrine, forsake ye not my law.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4></TD><TD><P>For I was my father's son, tender   
and only beloved in the sight of my mother.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A  
NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>He taught me also, and said unto me, Let thine    
heart retain my words: keep my commandments, and live.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD><P>Get wisdom, get understanding:      
forget it not; neither decline from the words of my mouth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>Forsake her not, and she shall      
preserve thee: love her, and she shall keep thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD          
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>Wisdom is the principal thing;      
therefore get wisdom: and with all thy getting get understanding.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>Exalt her, and she shall    
promote thee: she shall bring thee to honour, when thou dost embrace her.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>She shall give to 
thine head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to thee.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear, O my son, 
and receive my sayings; and the years of thy life shall be many.</P></TD></TR>  
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>I have taught thee in the 
way of wisdom; I have led thee in right paths.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>When thou goest, thy steps shall not be      
straitened; and when thou runnest, thou shalt not stumble.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Take fast hold of instruction;    
let her not go: keep her; for she is thy life.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Enter not into the path of the wicked, and   
go not in the way of evil men.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4> 
15</H4></TD><TD><P>Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>For they sleep  
not, except they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they 
cause some to fall.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD>
<TD><P>For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD><P>But the path of 
the just is as the shining light, that shineth more and more unto the perfect   
day.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19><H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>The way 
of the wicked is as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>My son, attend to my      
words; incline thine ear unto my sayings.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD><P>Let them not depart from thine eyes; keep them  
in the midst of thine heart.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>   
22</H4></TD><TD><P>For they are life unto those that find them, and health to   
all their flesh.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>Keep thy heart with all diligence; for out of it are the issues of       
life.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD><P>Put    
away from thee a froward mouth, and perverse lips put far from thee.</P></TD>   
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>25</H4></TD><TD><P>Let thine eyes look  
right on, and let thine eyelids look straight before thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V26><H4>26</H4></TD><TD><P>Ponder the path of thy feet, and  
let all thy ways be established.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V27>   
<H4>27</H4></TD><TD><P>Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove thy   
foot from evil.</P></TD></TR></TABLE><!--This Software is copyright 2000 by     
